    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a fair assessment of the volatility. I'm curious about the specific drivers behind the \"risk\" in Profile B. When you see those shifts in community composition and demographics during a period of rapid change, what specific factors usually lead to the devaluation or instability you're describing? Is it more about the economic status of the new residents or the social cohesion of the area?",
